2 3 for writing credit or b class participation including a final in class presentation 1 3 and a research paper 2 3 for research credit students who wish to receive research credit must obtain permission from the professor before submitting the request to the registrar's office number of units 3 course number 476 recently taught by daniel barton thomas j nolan all civil procedure and litigation courses administrative law advanced criminal practice civil jury constitutional litigation evidence federal courts federal indian law federal pretrial litigation mediation moot court kirkwood competition psychology of litigation practical and ethical implications reconstructing the administrative state theory and practice scientific evidence and expert testimony patent litigation supreme court litigation clinic trial advocacy workshop all criminal law and procedure courses advanced criminal practice criminal defense clinic criminal procedure adjudication criminal procedure investigation criminal prosecution clinic evidence externship companion seminar international criminal law sentencing corrections and criminal justice policy supreme court simulation seminar white collar crime related links axess coursework digital reserve sls registrar mostly cloudy 50 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
